ed meaning.” Human being is inseparable from animality.This book differs from other studies of Merleau-Ponty by emphasizing his lifelong attention to science. It shows how his attention to evolutionary biology and ethology anticipated recent studies of animal cognition, culture, and communication.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAnimals (Philosophy). 4aAnimal Studies. 4aEnvironment. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aBacchae.  aGilgamesh.  aLife of Pi.  aMeleau_Ponty.  aanimal studies.  aanimality.  aanimals and culture.  aanimals.  ahuman evolution.  alanguage.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311070729840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823255689zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823255689423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823255689/original  a978-3-11-070729-8  Fordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK